SEARCH
Package com.app.txt.transfer

Interface Transfer<T,U>

Type Parameters:
T - the type of keys used in the data.
U - the type of values associated with the keys.
All Known Implementing Classes:
TransferImpl
public interface Transfer<T,U>
Interface for transferring data to and from a file. This interface provides methods for reading data from a file into a map of keys and values, and for writing data to a file.

  • Method Details

    • read

      Map<T,List<U>> read(String filename, LineParser<T,U> lineParser)
      Reads data from the specified file and parses it into a map of keys and values. Uses the provided LineParser to parse each line of the file into key-value pairs.
      Parameters:
      filename - the name of the file to read from.
      lineParser - the LineParser instance used to parse lines into key-value pairs.
      Returns:
      a map where the keys are of type T and the values are lists of items of type U.

    • write

      void write(String filename, T t, Function<T,String> prepare)
      Writes data to the specified file using the provided function to prepare the data for writing. The data is converted into a string format suitable for writing by applying the provided function.
      Parameters:
      filename - the name of the file to write to.
      t - the data to write.
      prepare - a Function that converts the data into a string format suitable for writing.
